The paper deals with the complexity of a graph coloring problem, which is a fundamental topic in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The problem is related to graph homomorphism and Kneser graphs, which are topics in computational geometry and combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
